{% extends 'layout.twig' %} {% block content %}

<section
  class="mt-16 mb-16 flex flex-col gap-8 lg:gap-10 mx-4 lg:items-center lg:mx-0"
>
  <h1 class="text-center font-semibold tracking-tight text-xl">
    Privacy Policy
  </h1>
  <div class="max-w-3xl text-lg space-y-6 [&>h2]:font-bold">
    <p class="text-sm">Last updated: 2025-11-20</p>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how
      <strong>{{ app_name }}</strong> (“we”, “us”, or “our”) collects, uses, and
      protects your personal data when you use our website and services. We are
      committed to complying with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
      and respecting your privacy.
    </p>

    <p>
      By using {{ app_name }}, you agree to the practices described in this
      policy.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      We collect only the data necessary to provide and improve the service.
    </p>

    <h3>1.1 Account Information</h3>
    <p>You may create an account in two ways:</p>

    <p>a) Username / Email + Password</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Password (stored securely and hashed)</li>
      <li>Your saved TV shows and preferences</li>
    </ul>

    <p>b) Google Sign-In</p>
    <p>If you sign up using Google, Google provides us with:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Your Google account email address</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do <strong>not</strong> receive access to your Google password or other
      Google account data.
    </p>

    <p>
      An additional password will be stored if you enable notifications via
      ntfy.
    </p>
    <p>If you enable Discord notifications, the Discord webhook url 
      you provide will be encrypted and stored.
    </p>

    <h3>1.2 Cookies and Local Storage</h3>
    <p>
      We use only <strong>essential cookies</strong> and local storage to
      support:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Keeping you logged in (session management)</li>
      <li>
        Storing your show list locally if you use the site without an account
      </li>
      <li>Basic website functionality</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These cookies are strictly necessary and do <strong>not</strong> require
      user consent under GDPR.
    </p>

    <h3>1.3 Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong>, a privacy-friendly,
      cookie-free analytics tool. It:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Does not use cookies</li>
      <li>Does not track users across sites</li>
      <li>Does not collect personal identifiers</li>
      <li>Provides only aggregated, anonymous statistics</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <p>We use your data only for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Providing your account and watchlist</li>
      <li>Allowing login via Google or email/password</li>
      <li>Operating and improving the service</li>
      <li>Understanding general usage through anonymous analytics</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data or use it for advertising or
      profiling.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Legal Bases for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>
        <strong>Contractual necessity</strong> — providing your account and
        watchlist
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — site security, performance, and
        analytics
      </li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> — compliance where required</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>We only share your data with essential service providers, including:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Hosting providers</li>
      <li>Cloudflare (security and analytics)</li>
      <li>Google (for authentication, only when you choose Google sign-in)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These providers follow GDPR requirements. We do
      <strong>not</strong> share data with advertisers.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain data only as long as necessary:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Account data:</strong> kept until you delete your account</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Local storage / essential cookies:</strong> stored until cleared
        by you
      </li>
      <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> aggregated and non-identifying</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Deleting your account permanently removes your personal data.</p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Access your personal data</li>
      <li>Request corrections</li>
      <li>Request deletion (“right to be forgotten”)</li>
      <li>Restrict processing in certain circumstances</li>
      <li>Receive a data export (data portability)</li>
      <li>Object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise these rights, contact us at:
      <strong>{{ app_email }}</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>We use industry-standard security measures, including:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Encrypted connections (HTTPS)</li>
      <li>Secure password hashing</li>
      <li>Server-side access controls</li>
      <li>Cloudflare security protections</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      While no system is completely secure, we take appropriate steps to protect
      your data and will notify you of any breach.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Cookies and Consent</h2>
    <p>
      Because we use only essential cookies and cookie-free analytics, a GDPR
      cookie consent banner is
      <strong>not required</strong>. We still disclose our cookie usage in this
      policy for transparency.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Account Deletion and Data Export</h2>
    <p>
      You may delete your account at any time, which permanently removes your
      data. You may also request a machine-readable export of the data you
      provided.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. When changes occur, the
      updated version will be posted with a revised “Last updated” date.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or requests, contact us at:</p>
    <p><strong>Email: </strong>{{ app_email }}</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}
